In Git:--
<br>

For configration:-

git config --global user.name "xyz..."

git config --global user.email "xyz@ =gmail.com"

For Colour UI:-

git config --global color.ui auto


Now Use VS Code Editor:

Open terminal in, VS Code..

For Check git:- type 

git --version (your git version)

Now, Cloning Git Repo in VS code editor by code:-

git clone <u> Copy hear ur git repo https address</u>

<B>Now done any update and add in ur git repo by help of the VS Code </b>

After updation check Status ur Git repo by...

git status

For addding updates in git use...

git add <ufile name>

git add . (<u>for all files add</u>)

for modify & commit...

git commit -m "write reason of commitment.."

for push the modification in git repo...

git push origin main